
Outline of adding a vm watch:

  vm.append_hack([:watch_path :key [Term#123]])
  vm.run
  vm.get_watch_result(:key)

When running the interpreter:

  When walking through the hack list
    Store information on the watch in cachedValues
    Find the target block, load the StackBlock and store a flag "hasWatch"
    When generating term bytecode, in the post-term step, if the term has a watch
      on it, then append a CheckWatch instruction.

Inside CheckWatch
  Generate stack path
  Load watch value by index
  Check if stack path equals target
  If so, copy value to watch

New function Stack.get_watch_result
  Use byWatchKey to find value inside cachedValues

In BytecodeCache
  Add byWatchKey

Bytecode
  New instruction CheckWatch
